<TEXT>
police using federal and local laws to create 
drug free zones around schools swept through neighborhoods 
thursday and arrested 83 people and confiscated drugs and guns 
including an ak47 assault rifle 
the 12hour sweep was conducted by 250 police officers who posed 
as drug buyers near 15 elementary and junior high schools 
people are shocked to learn that most heavy drug trafficking 
areas in los angeles are around our schools said district 
attorney ira reiner after the sweep 
the youngest person arrested was 14 and perhaps the craftiest 
was a 17yearold alleged drug dealer who had adults working for 
him said deputy chief glenn levant 
ten guns including the assault rifle were seized along with 
155 grams of rock cocaine the smokable form also known as crack 
levant said 
us attorney robert bonner said 29 of those arrested during the 
action will be investigated for violating a federal law against 
selling illegal drugs within 1000 feet of a school the charge 
carries a minimum sentence of one year in prison and a maximum of 
40 years 
the remaining cases will be investigated by the district 
attorney he said he estimated that about 35 percent of the 
suspects are gang members 
this is a program designed to foster and create drugfree 
zones around our schools bonner said 
</TEXT>
