<TEXT>
novelist naguib mahfouz of egypt who 
chronicled mans search for values in stories set from the nile 
delta of the pharaohs to the busy streets of modern cairo today 
won the 1988 nobel prize for literature 
the 76yearold retired civil servant who once had his work 
banned in his native country was the first arabiclanguage writer 
to win the award 
i am happy extremely happy for myself and for arab 
literature mahfouz was quoted as saying by the governments 
