the manager of the troubled savannah river 
plant has taken a leave of absence for medical reasons pending his 
retirement according to the du pont co which operates the 
nuclear complex 
du pont spokesman jim felder said there was no connection 
between the departure of srp general manager john t granaghan 59 
and problems with the plants reactors 
granaghans leave of absence pending his retirement after 38 
years with du pont was due to medical reasons felder said 
its a personal matter mr granaghan had surgery earlier this 
year felder said 
john t lowe director of the savannah river laboratory will 
succeed granaghan as plant manager felder said 
the plants three reactors were reduced to halfpower late last 
year when experts questioned whether the emergency cooling system 
could cope with an emergency at full power 
since april all three reactors have been shut down entirely for 
maintenance and testing amid additional safety questions 
when closed srp was the sole producer of tritium and plutonium 
used by the military in nuclear weapons the only other 
manufacturer the hanford nuclear reservation in washington state 
has been shut down for more than a year 
westinghouse electric co is scheduled to assume operation of 
