one missing piece in the jigsaw sought by some hostile intelligence 
agency he wrote 
donald trelford editor of the observer estimated the 
government would have to pay 35 million in legal fees the 
government puts the bill at 1 million 
the government first moved against the book in september 1985 
when it obtained a temporary injunction preventing publication in 
australia 
that case was resolved only in june when australias highest 
