ferdinand marcos fostered unrest against his 
own government to justify dictatorial powers according to a 
journal handwritten by the ousted philippine president the los 
angeles times reported thursday 
i have that feeling of certainty that i will end up with 
dictatorial powers if the situation continues and the situation 
will continue marcos wrote in 1970 
the papers indicate that marcos deceived us officials who have 
long sought good relations with the philippines because of the 
countrys strategic location and vast us military installations 
for example marcos told ambassador henry a byroade that he 
suspected china of supplying arms to maoist revolutionaries just a 
