foreign powers were providing the revolutionaries with arms the 
times said 
the papers are reportedly part of a larger manuscript discovered 
in the presidential palace after marcos fled manila in the 
bloodless revolution that brought corazon aquino to power in 
february 1986 
marcos lives in exile in hawaii his spokesman gemmo trinidad 
blasted the papers release as an invasion of privacy and said 
marcos may go to court over it 
the papers also show that marcos expected maoist rebels would 
try to spark a revolution but he acknowledged that they and other 
groups were weak 
we should allow them to gather strength but not such strength 
that we cannot overcome them a feb 17 1970 entry says 
marcos worked his plan for absolute power cautiously the papers 
