by march 1970 however marcos was losing patience as nonviolent 
demonstrations were not disruptive enough for him the papers say 
the disorders must now be induced into a crisis so stricter 
measures can be taken a march 3 1970 entry says 
another entry says a little more destruction and vandalism 
and i can do anything 
james miller an independent handwriting analyst hired by the 
newspaper checked them against formal degrees written by marcos 
and found virtually everything was consistent 
the entries start on new years eve of 1970 just after marcos 
was reelected to his second term as president in an election 
marked by allegations of vote fraud 
