a un cambodia resolution calls for the 
10th straight year for withdrawal of vietnamese forces but this 
time also specifies nonreturn of pol pots genocidal policies 
in trying for a breakthrough 
increasingly the issue of khmer rouge leader pol pot and how to 
prevent his return to power is seen as a major stumbling block in 
achieving a vietnamese troop withdrawal a political settlement and 
a nonaligned cambodia 
chinas un mission indicated on tuesday that the beijing 
government could accept pol pot and his circle as refugees under 
chinese law but the statement did not specifically mention the 
ailing communist leader 
although a formal offer of refuge for pol pot has not been made 
and details remain to be worked out diplomats here see chinas new 
willingness to offer sanctuary as a major positive development in 
resolving the problem 
china has been a strong supporter and arms supplier of the khmer 
rouge the strongest antivietnamese fighting force but has 
distanced itself from pol pots policies 
the cambodia resolution has been adopted overwhelmingly every 
year since the december 1978 invasion of cambodia by vietnamese 
troops to oust pol pot who presided over the deaths of at least 1 
million cambodians in the 1970s 
the united nations is expected to play a major role in any 
cambodian settlement possibly providing a peacekeeing force and 
observers to supervise a vietnamese troop withdrawal and free 
elections 
the noncommunist association of southeast asian nations asean 
has been drafting the resolution for 10 years it introduced major 
changes this year to reflect the dialogue between cambodian 
factions and the desire to exclude pol pot from any major role in 
cambodia 
the khmer rouge led by khieu samphan is the strongest of three 
factions fighting the vietnamese the others are noncommunist 
factions led by former cambodian prime minister son sann and prince 
norodom sihanouk the prince is expected to become the head of a 
future coalition government 
the resolution last year was adopted by a vote of 117 to 21 
with 16 abstentions 
this year the yes vote could be even higher according to 
asian diplomats while vietnam the soviet union and their friends 
are expected to oppose it again the reference to excluding pol pot 
is considered a welcome change 
the draft resolution calls for the following new elements 
the nonreturn to the universally condemned policies and 
practices of a recent past a reference to the documented deaths 
blamed on the pol pot regime the passage is taken directly from 
the secretarygenerals own report on cambodia issued oct 17 1985 
the khmer rouge and others call that reference an unacceptable 
interference in cambodias internal affairs but asian diplomats 
familiar with the resolution say the secretarygenerals own 
language carries considerable weight and will be difficult to 
change 
the effective international supervision and control of the 
withdrawal of about 130000 vietnamese troops and effective 
guarantees providing for a pullout 
an interim administering authority or a coalition 
government also bolstered by effective guarantees by the 
international community 
the promotion of national reconciliation among all cambodians 
under the leadership of samdech norodom sihanouk 
a future coalition government is expected to include the three 
cambodian factions fighting the vietnamese as well as the 
vietnameseinstalled government in phnom penh 
asian diplomats speaking on condition of anonymity say china 
is not enthusiastic about the language condemning khmer rouge 
atrocities but it strongly opposes vietnams occupation of 
cambodia and is expected to support the resolution again 
a draft copy of the resolution was provided to the associated 
press by foreign diplomats and the document was expected to be 
formally introduced friday or early next week 
