<DOCNO> AP881013-0362 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
president jose sarney on thursday fired 
the central bank director responsible for a massive jump in money 
market interest rates that caused stock prices to tumble and 
sparked a frenzy of rumors in financial markets 
sarney fired juarez soares after the director boosted the 
monthly interest rate on overnight money market investments from 39 
percent to 50 percent causing chaos when markets opened thursday 
according to presidential palace spokesman carlos de almeida santos 
the rate is adjusted daily 
soares told sarney he had hoped to steer investors away from 
nonmoney assets such as stocks property and gold and back into 
cash santos said higher interest rates increase the 
attractiveness of assets denominated in cruzados the brazilian 
currency 
in recent months investors have opted for noncruzado assets to 
protect themselves from steadilyrising inflation which is 
projected at 26 percent this month the stock market and the value 
of such investments have risen substantially 
but the market interpreted soares move as an indication of a 
much higher than expected inflation for this month creating a wave 
of panic and rumors that finance minister mailson da nobrega would 
be dismissed santos said 
in rio de janeiro the stock market closed down 38 percent 
technically the measure was right but soares chose a bad 
moment said geraldo moura a spokesman for the finance ministry 
inflation is high and there is a generalized instability 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

